<H2><U>
Native American Mermaid Stories
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/Ne-Hwas-The-Mermaid-Passamaquoddy.html
">Ne Hwas, the Indian Mermaid</a>:</B> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Passamaquoddy tale of two girls who turned into mermaids.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-137.html#sun
">The Men Who Visited the Sun</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Potawatomi legend about the origin of the first merman.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.lenapenation.org/The%20Lost%20Boy.pdf
">The Lost Boy</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Delaware story about a boy who married a mermaid.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.calverley.ca/Part06-Legends/6-003.html
">Legend of the Mermaid</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Sekani Indian legend about a man who married a mermaid.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.calverley.ca/Part06-Legends/6-003.html
">Mermaid Tales from Native Tribes Abound</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Synopses of Indian mermaid legends from several different tribes.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books about Mermaids in Native American Mythology</a>
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0888544294/natilangofthe-20
">Mermaids and Medicine Women</a>:</B> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Interesting book of Ojibwe folktales about mermaids and other female spirits, told by a Native author.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0822599813/natilangofthe-20
">Mermaids and Mermen</a>:</B> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Good kids' collection of mermaid stories from world mythology, including Native American lore.
<BR>

